      <h2>Safety</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        Read all safety warnings, instructions, illustrations and specifications provided with this power tool. Failure to follow them may result in electric shock, fire, and/or serious injury.
      </div>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Wear hearing protection</strong> when impact (hammer) drilling &mdash; exposure to noise can cause hearing loss.</li>
        <li><strong>Hold the tool by the insulated grip surfaces</strong> when the bit may contact hidden wiring. A live wire contacting metal parts will energize the tool.</li>
        <li>Use safety glasses meeting ANSI Z87.1 (CAN/CSA Z94.3). Everyday eyeglasses are not safety glasses.</li>
        <li>Hammer bits and the chuck get hot during operation &mdash; wear gloves when touching them.</li>
        <li>Always start a long bit with the tip in contact with the workpiece. At higher RPM a free‑spinning bit will bend.</li>
        <li>Apply pressure only in line with the bit. Side pressure or excess force can break the bit and cause loss of control.</li>
        <li>Clamp or otherwise secure the workpiece. Holding work by hand or against your body is unstable.</li>
        <li>Remove the battery pack before changing accessories or making adjustments.</li>
        <li>Do not use this tool to mix or pump combustible or explosive fluids (benzine, alcohol, etc.).</li>
      </ul>

